text.section:
The board may refuse to issue a license, or suspend, revoke, impose probationary conditions, impose an administrative fine, issue a written reprimand, or any combination thereof regarding any licensee upon proof that the licensee or applicant has:
Violated any provision of KRS 329A.010 to 329A.090 or any administrative regulation promulgated by the board;
Knowingly and willfully made a material misstatement in connection with an application for license or renewal;
Been convicted of a felony;
Practiced fraud, deceit, or misrepresentation;
Committed any act that would have been cause for refusal to issue the license had it existed and been known to the board at the time of issuance;
Been incompetent or negligent in the practice of private investigating; or
Violated the code of ethics promulgated by administrative regulation by the board.
